{
  "texts": [
    "The main absorption mechanism of our system is Ohmic loss on the metallic walls; the absorption is hence distributed rather than spatially localized.",
    "The metasurface is in a known configuration c that is chosen randomly and has not been part of the calibration data set.",
    "ψ in is normalized so that its 2-norm is unity.",
    "Let the eigenvalues of the Hermitian matrix S y S be denoted by s n, where 0 ≤ s 1 ≤ s 2 ≤ s 3 ≤ s 4 ≤ 1, and the corresponding eigenvectors are v n.",
    "The reflected wave energy exiting the scattering system is R = jSψ in j 2 and the absorbed energy is 1 À R. The provably optimal input wavefront for coherently enhanced absorption is ψ opt in = v 1, i.e., the eigenvector of S y S that is associated with the eigenvalue of smallest magnitude 45."
  ]
}